## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="bed3e-152">O exemplo a seguir cria uma gramática de reconhecimento de fala usando <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Choices> e <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.GrammarBuilder> objetos.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="bed3e-152">The following example creates a speech recognition grammar using <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Choices> and <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.GrammarBuilder> objects.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="bed3e-153">O <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar.%23ctor%2A> construtor cria um <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar> objeto o <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.GrammarBuilder> objeto.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="bed3e-153">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar.%23ctor%2A> constructor creates a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar> object from the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.GrammarBuilder> object.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
  
// Create a grammar using a GrammarBuilder and return the new grammar.   
private static Grammar CreateGrammarBuilderGrammar()  
{  
  GrammarBuilder builder = new GrammarBuilder();  
  
  Choices cityChoice = new Choices (new string[]   
  {"Seattle", "New York", "Miami", "Los Angeles"});  
  
  builder.Append("I would like to fly from");  
  builder.Append(cityChoice);  
  builder.Append("to");  
  builder.Append(cityChoice);  
  
  Grammar citiesGrammar = new Grammar(builder);  
  citiesGrammar.Name = "GrammarBuilder Cities Grammar";  
  
  return citiesGrammar;  
}  
```

  
  
